obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE CHILD AND ADOLESCENT (PROHIBITION AND REGULATION) ACT, 1986`
  line ________
  line `ARRANGEMENT OF SECTIONS`
  line ________
  line `PART I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement.`
  line `2. Definitions.`
  line `PART II`
  line `P ROHIBITION OF EMPLOYMENT OF CHILDREN IN CERTAIN OCCUPATIONS AND PROCESSES`
  line `3. Prohibition of employment of children in any occupation and process.`
  line `3A. Prohibition of employment of adolescents in certain hazardous occupations and process es.`
  line `4. Power to amend the Schedule.`
  line `5. Technical Advisory Committee.`
  line `PART III`
  line `R EGULATION OF CONDITIONS OF WORK OF CHILDREN`
  line `6. Application of Part.`
  line `7. Hours and period of work.`
  line `8. Weekly holidays.`
  line `9. Notice to Inspector.`
  line `10. Disputes as to age.`
  line `11. Maintenance of register.`
  line `12. Display of notice containing abstract of sections 3 and 14.`
  line `13. Health and safety.`
  line `PART IV`
  line `M ISCE LLANEOUS`
  line `14. Penalties.`
  line `14A. Offences to be Congnizable.`
  line `14B. Child and Adolescent Labour Rehabilitation Fund.`
  line `14C. Rehabilitation of rescued child or adolescent.`
  line `14D. Compounding of offences.`
  line `15. Modified application of certain laws in relation to penalties.`
  line `16. Proc edure relating to offences.`
  line `17. Appointment of Inspectors.`
  line `17A. District Magistrate to implement the provisions.`
  line `17B. Inspection and monitoring.`
  line `18. Power to make rules.`
  line `19. Rules and notifications to be laid before Parliament or State legislature.`
  line `20. Certain other provisions of law not barred.`
  line `21. Power to remove difficulties.`
  line `22. Repeal and savings.`
  line `23 to 26 [ Repealed. ]`
  line `THE SCHEDULE.`
