obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `THE CHILD AND ADOLESCENT LABOUR (PROHIB ITION AND REGULATION) ACT,`
  line 1986
  line `A CT N O. 61 OF 1986`
  line `[23 rd December, 1986.]`
  line `1 [ An Act to prohibit the engagement of children in all occupations and to prohibit the engagement`
  line `of adolescents in hazardous occupations and processes and the matters connected therewith or`
  line `incidental thereto.]`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Thirty - seventh Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `PART I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called 2 [ the Child and Adolescent`
  line `Labour (Prohibition and Regulation) Act, 1986 ].`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of this Act, other than Part III, shall come into force at once, and Part III shall come`
  line `into force on such date 3 as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint,`
  line `and different dates may be appointed for different States and fo r different classes of establishments.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless t he context otherwise requires, —`
  line `4 [ ( i a ) ] “ appropriate Government ” means, in relation to an establishment under the control of the`
  line `Central Government or a railway administration or a major port or a mine or oilfield, the Central`
  line `Government, and in all othe r cases, the State Government;`
  line `5 [( i ) “adolescent” means a person w ho has completed his fourteenth year of age but has not`
  line `completed his eighteenth year;]`
  line `6 [ ( ii ) “ child ” means a person who has not comple ted his fourteenth year of age or such age as may`
  line `be specified in the Right of Children to Free and Compulsory Education Act, 2009 (35 of 2009),`
  line `whichever is more; ]`
  line `( iii ) “ day ” means a period of twenty - fou r hours beginning at mid - night;`
  line `( iv ) “ establishment ” includes a shop, commercial establishment, workshop, farm, residential hotel,`
  line `restaurant, eating house, theatre or other place of pub lic amusement or entertainment;`
  line `( v ) “ family ”, in relation to an occupier, means the individual, the wife or husband, as th e case may`
  line `be, of such individual, and their children, brothe r or sister of such individual;`
  line `( vi ) “ occupier ”, in relation to an establishment or a workshop, means the person who has the`
  line `ultimate control over the affairs of the establishment or workshop;`
  line `( v ii ) “ port authority ” means any authority administe ring a port;`
  line `( viii ) “ prescribed ” means prescribed by rules made under section 18;`
  line `( ix ) “ week ” means a period of seven days beginning at midnight on Saturday night or such other`
  line `night as may be approved in w riting for a pa rticular area by the Inspector;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 35 of 2016, s. 2, for the long title (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “the Child Labour (Prohibition and Regulation) Act, 1986 (61 of 1986) ” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `3. 26th May, 1993, vide notification No. S.O. 333(E), dated 26th March, 1993, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3( ii ).`
  line `4. Clause ( i ) renumbered as clause ( ia ) thereof by Act 35 of 20 16, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e. f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-3
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Page 3`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  sourcePage 3
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `( x ) “ workshop ” means any premises (including the precincts thereof) wherein any indus t rial`
  line `process is carried on, but does not include any premises to which the provisions of section 67 of the`
  line `Factories Act, 1 948 (63 of 1948), for the time being, apply.`
  line `PART II`
  line `P ROHIBITION OF EMPLOYMENT OF CHILDREN IN CERTAIN OCCUPATIONS AND PROCESSES`
  line `1 [ 3. Prohibition of employment of children in any occupation and process. — ( 1 ) No child shall be`
  line `employed or permitted t o work in any occupation or process.`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing in sub - section ( 1 ) shall apply where the child, —`
  line `( a ) helps his family or family enterprise, which is other than any hazardous occupations or`
  line `processes set forth in the Schedule, after his s chool hours or during vacat ions;`
  line `( b ) works as an arti st in an audio - visual entertainment industry, including advertisement, films,`
  line `television serials or any such other entertainment or sports activities except the circus, subject to such`
  line `conditions and safe t y measures, as may be pre scribed:`
  line `Provided that no such work under t his clause shall effect the school education of the c hild.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the expression,`
  line `( a ) “family” in relation to a child, means his mother, father,brother, sister an d father’s sister`
  line `and brother and mother’s sister and brother;`
  line `( b ) “family enterprises” means any work, profession, manufacture or business which is`
  line `performed by the members of the family with the engagement of other persons;`
  line `( c ) “artist” means a child who performs or practices any work as a hobby or profession directly`
  line `involving him as an actor, singer, sports person or in such other activity as may be prescribed`
  line `relating to the entertainment or sports activities falling under clause ( b ) of sub - section`
  line `( 2 ).]`
  line `2 [ 3A. Prohibition of employment of adolescents in certain hazardous occupations and`
  line `process es. — No adolescent shall be employed or permitted to work in any of the hazardous occupations or`
  line `processes set forth in the Schedule:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, specify the nature of the non - hazardous`
  line `work to which an adolescent may be permitted to work under this Act.]`
  line `4. Power to amend the Schedule. — The Central Government, after giving by notif ication in the`
  line `Official Gazette, not less than three months ’ notice of its intention so to do, may, by like notification, 3 [ add`
  line `to, or, omit from, the Schedule any hazardous occupation or process ] and thereupon the Schedule shall be`
  line `deemed to have been amended accordingly.`
  line `5. 4 [ Technical Advisory Committee ]. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, constitute an advisory committee to be called the 4 [ Technical Advisory Committee ]`
  line `(hereafter in this section referred to as the Committee) to advise the Central Government for the purpose of`
  line `addition of occupations and processes to the Schedule.`
  line `( 2 ) The Committee shall consist of a Chairman and such other members not exceeding ten, as may be`
  line `appoi nted by the Central Government.`
  line `( 3 ) The Committee shall meet as often as it may consider necessary and shall have power to regulat e`
  line `its own procedure.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 35 of 2016, s. 5, for section 3 (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 201 6 ).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for “ add any occupation or process to the Schedule ” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for “Child Labour Technical Advisory Committee” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-4
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Page 4`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `( 4 ) The Committee may, if it deems it necessary so to do, constitute one o r more sub - committees a nd`
  line `may appoint to any such sub - committee, whether generally or for the consideration of any particular matter,`
  line `any person who is not a member of the Committee.`
  line `( 5 ) The term of office of, the manner of filling casual vacancies in the office of, and the allowances, if`
  line `any, payable to, the Chairman and other members of the Committee, and the conditions and restrictions`
  line `subject to which the Committee may appoint any person who is not a member of the Committee as a`
  line `member of any of its su b - committees shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line `PART III`
  line `R EGULATION OF CONDITIONS OF WORK OF 1 [ADOLESCENTS]`
  line `6. Application of Part. — The provisions of this Part shall apply to an establishment or a class of`
  line `establishments in which none of the occupations or processes referred to in 2 [ section 3 A] is carried on.`
  line `7. Hours and period of work. — ( 1 ) No 3 [adolescent] shall be required or permit ted to work in any`
  line `establishment in excess of such number of hours as may be prescribed for such establishm ent or class of`
  line establishments.
  line `( 2 ) The period of work on each day shall be so fixed that no period shall exceed three hours and that`
  line `no 3 [adolescent ] shall work for more than three hours before he has had an interval for rest for at least one`
  line hour.
  line `( 3 ) The period of work of a 3 [adolescent] shall be so arranged that inclusive of his interval for rest,`
  line `under sub - section ( 2 ), it shall not be spread over more than six hours, including the time spent in waiting`
  line `f or work on any day.`
  line `( 4 ) No 3 [ adolescent] shall be permitted or required t o work between 7 p.m. and 8 a.m.`
  line `( 5 ) No 3 [ adolescent] shall be required or permitted to work overtime.`
  line `( 6 ) No 3 [adolescent] shall be required or permitted to work in any establishment on any day on which`
  line `he has already been working in another establishment.`
  line `8. Weekly holidays. — Every 4 [adolescent] employed in an establishment shall be allowed in each`
  line `week, a holiday of one whole day, which day shall be specified by the occupier in a notice permanently`
  line `exhibited in a conspicuous place in the establishment and the day so specified shall not be altere d by the`
  line `occupier more than once in three months.`
  line `9. Notice to Inspector. — ( 1 ) Every occupier in relation to an establishment in which a 5 [adolescent]`
  line `was employed or permitted to work immediately before the date of commencement of this Act in relation`
  line `to s uch establishment shall, within a period of thirty days from such commence ment, send to the Inspector`
  line `within whose local limits the establishment is situated, a written notice containing the f ollowing particulars,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) the name and situation of the establishment;`
  line `( b ) the name of the person in actual m anagement of the establishment;`
  line `( c ) the address to which communications relating to the establishment should be sent; and`
  line `( d ) the nature of the occupation or process carried on in the establishment.`
  line `( 2 ) Every occupier, in relation to an establishment, who employs, or permits to work, any 5 [adolescent]`
  line `after the date of commencement of this Act in relation to such establishment, shall, within a period of thirty`
  line `days from the date of such employment, sen d to the Inspector within whose local limits the establishment`
  line `is situated, a written notice containing the particulars as are mentioned in sub - section ( 1 ).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 35 of 2016, s. 9, for “CHILDREN” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for “section 3” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for “child” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for “child” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for “child” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of sub - sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), “ date of commencement of this Act, in`
  line `relation to an establishment ” means the date of bringing into force of this Act in relation to such`
  line establishment.
  line `( 3 ) Nothing in sections 7, 8 and 9 shall apply to any establishment wherein any process is carried on by`
  line `the occupier with t he aid of his family or to any school established by, or receiving assistance or recognition`
  line `from, Government.`
  line `10. Disputes as to age. — I f any question arises between an Inspector and an occupier as to the age of`
  line `any 1 [adolescent] who is employed or is permitted to work by him in an establishment, the question shall,`
  line `in the absence of a certificate as to the age of such 1 [adolescent] granted by the prescribed medical authority,`
  line `be referred by the Inspector for decision to the presc ribed medical authority.`
  line `11. Maintenance of register. — There shall be maintained by every occupier in respect of 2 [adolescent]`
  line `employed or permitted to work in any establishment, a register to be available for inspection by an Inspector`
  line `at all times during working hours or when work is being carried on in a ny such establishment, showing —`
  line `( a ) the name and date of birth of every 3 [adolescent] so employed or permitted to work;`
  line `( b ) hours and periods of work of any such 3 [adolescent] and the intervals of rest to which he is`
  line entitled;
  line `( c ) the nature of work of any such 3 [adolescent]; and`
  line `( d ) such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line `12. Display of notice containing abstract of 4 [ sections 3 A and 14 ]. — Every railway administration,`
  line `every port authority and every occupier shall cause to be displayed in a conspicuous and accessible place`
  line `at every station on its railway or within the limits of a port or at the place of work, as the case may be, a`
  line `notice in the local language and in the English language containing an abstract of 4 [ sections 3 A and 14 ].`
  line `13. Health and safety. — ( 1 ) The appropriate Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for the health and safety of the 5 [adolescen t ] employed or permitted to work in any establishment`
  line `or class of establishments.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the said rules may provide for all`
  line `or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) cleanliness in the place o f work and its freedom from nuisance;`
  line `( b ) di sposal of wastes and effluents;`
  line `( c ) ventilat ion and temperature;`
  line `( d ) dust and fume;`
  line `( e ) artificial humidification;`
  line `( f ) lighting;`
  line `( g ) drinking water;`
  line `( h ) latrine and urinals;`
  line `( i ) spittoons;`
  line `( j ) fencing of machinery;`
  line `( k ) work at or near machinery in motion;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 35 of 2016, s. 14, for “child” (w.e.f 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for “children” (w.e.f 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for “child” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for “section 3 and 14” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for “children” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `( l ) employment of 1 [adolescent] on dangerous mach ines;`
  line `( m ) instructions, training and supervision in relation to employment of 1 [adolescent] on dangerous`
  line machines;
  line `( n ) device for cutting off power;`
  line `( o ) self - acting machines;`
  line `( p ) easing of new machinery;`
  line `( q ) flo or, stairs and means of access;`
  line `( r ) pits, sumps, o penings in floors, etc.;`
  line `( s ) excessive weights;`
  line `( t ) protection of eyes;`
  line `( u ) explosive or inflammable dust, gas, etc.;`
  line `( v ) precautions in case of fir e;`
  line `( w ) maintenance of buildings; and`
  line `( x ) safety of buildings and machinery.`
  line `PART IV`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `14. Penalties. — 2 [ ( 1 ) Whoever employs any child or permits any child to work in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of section 3 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six`
  line `months but which may extend to two years, or with fine which shall not be less than twenty thousand rupees`
  line `but which may extend to fifty thousand rupees, or with both:`
  line `Provided that the parents or gu ardians of such children shall not be punished unless they permit such`
  line `child for commercial purposes in contravention of the provisions of section 3.`
  line `( 1A ) Whoever employs any adolescent or permits any adolescent to work in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of section 3A shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six`
  line `months but which may extend to two years or with fine whic h shall not be less than twenty thousand rupees`
  line `but which may extend to fifty thousand rupees, or with both:`
  line `Provided that the parents or guardians of such adolescent shall not be punished unless they permit such`
  line `adolescent to work in contravention of the provisions of section 3A.`
  line `( 1B ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - sections ( 1 ) and (1A ) the parents or guardians of any`
  line `child or adolescent referred to in section 3 or section 3A, shall not be liable for punishment, in case of the`
  line `first offence.]`
  line `3 [ ( 2 ) Whoever, having been convicted of an offence under section 3 or section 3A commits a like`
  line `offence afterwards, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one`
  line `year but which may extend to three years.`
  line `( 2A ) Notwithsta nding anything contained in sub - section ( 2 ), the parents or guardian having been`
  line `convicted of an offence under section 3 or section 3A, commits a like offence afterwards, he shall be`
  line `punishable with a fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees.]`
  line `( 3 ) Whoever —`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 35 of 2016, s. 17, for “children” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for sub - section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for sub - section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `4. Clauses ( a ), ( b ) and ( c ) omitted by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Page 7`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `( d ) fails to comply with or contravenes any other provisions of this Ac t or the rules made`
  line thereunder,
  line `shall be punishable with simple imprisonment which may extend to one month or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupee s or with both.`
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line Gujarat
  line `Amendment of section 14 of 61 of 1986. — In the Child and Adolescent Labour (Prohibition and`
  line `Regulation) Act, 1986 (61 of 1986), in its application to the State of Gujarat (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `“the principal Act”), in section 14, -`
  line `(i) in sub - section (1), for the words “fifty thousand rupees”, the words “one lakh rupees” shall`
  line `be substituted;`
  line `(ii) in sub - section (1A), for the words “fifty thousand rupees”, the words “one lakh rupees”`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line `[ Vide Gujarat Act 19 of 2021, s. 2]`
  line `1 [ 14A. Offences to be Congnizable. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence committed by an employer and punishable under section 3 or`
  line `section 3A shall be cognizable.`
  line `14B. Child and Adolescent Labour Rehabilitation Fund. — ( 1 ) The appropriate Government shall`
  line `constitute a Fund in every district or for two or more distri cts to be called the Child and Adolescent Labour`
  line `Rehabilitation Fund to which the amount of the fine realized from the employer of the child and adolescent,`
  line `within the jurisdiction of such district o r districts, shall be credited.`
  line `( 2 ) The appropriate Gover nment shall credit an amount of fifteen thousand rupees to the Fund for each`
  line `child or adolescent for whom the fine amount has been credited under sub - section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3 ) The amount credited to the Fund under sub - sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) shall be deposited in suc h banks or`
  line `invested in such manner, as the appropriate Gov ernment may decide.`
  line `( 4 ) The amount deposited or invested, as the case may be under sub - section ( 3 ), and the interest accrued`
  line `on it, shall be paid to the child or adolescent in whose favour such amou nt is credited, in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line `Expla nation. — For the purposes of appropriate Government, the Central Government shall include the`
  line `Administrator or the Lieutenant Governor of a Union territory under article 239A of the Constitution.`
  line `1 4C. Rehabilitation of rescued child or adolescent. — The child or adolescent, who is employed in`
  line `contravention of the provisions of this Act and rescued, shall be rehabilitated in accordance with the laws`
  line `for the time being in force.`
  line `14D. Compounding of offence s. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the District Magistrate may, on the application of the accused person,`
  line `compound any offence committed for the first time by him, under sub - section ( 3 ) of section 14 or any`
  line `offence committed by an accused person being parent or a guardian, in such manner and on payment of`
  line `such amount to the appropriate Government, as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) If the accused fails to pay such amount for composition of the offenc e, then, the proceedings shall`
  line `be continued against such person in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) Where any offence is compounded before the institution of any prosecution, no prosecution shall`
  line `be instituted in relation to such offence, ag ainst the offender in relation to whom the offence is so`
  line compounded.
  line `( 4 ) Where the composition of any offence is made after the institution of any prosecution, such`
  line `composition shall be brought in writing, to the notice of the Court in which the prosecutio n is pending and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 2016, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `on the approval of the composition of the offence being given, the person against whom the offence is so`
  line `compounded, shall be discharged.]`
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line Gujarat
  line `Amendment of section 14D of 61 of 1986. - In the principal Act, in section 14D, in sub - section (1), for the`
  line `words “District Magistrate”, the words “District Magistrate, Municipal Commissioner, Director of Labour`
  line `or, as the case may be, the Regional Commissioner of Municipalities” shall be substitu ted.`
  line `[ Vide Gujarat Act 19 of 2021, s. 3]`
  line `15. Modified application of certain laws in relation to penalties. — ( 1 ) Where any person is found`
  line `guilty and convicted of cont ravention of any of the provisions mentioned in sub - section ( 2 ), he shall be`
  line `liable to penalties as provided in sub - sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) of section 14 of this Act and not under the Acts`
  line `in which those provisions are contained.`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) are the provisions mentioned below: —`
  line `( a ) section 67 of the Factori es Act, 1948 (63 of 1948);`
  line `( b ) section 40 of th e Mines Act, 1952 (35 of 195 2);`
  line `( c ) section 109 of the Merchant Shipp ing Act, 1958 (44 of 1958); and`
  line `( d ) section 21 of the Motor Transport Workers Act, 1961 (27 of 1961).`
  line `16. Procedure relating to offences. — ( 1 ) Any person, police officer or Inspector may file a complaint`
  line `of the commission of an offence under this Act in any c ourt of competent jurisdiction.`
  line `( 2 ) Every certificate as to the age of a child which has been granted by a prescribed medical authority`
  line `s hall, for the purposes of this Act, be conclusive evidence as to the age o f the child to whom it relates.`
  line `( 3 ) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Magistrate of the first class shall try any`
  line `offence under this Act.`
  line `17. Appointment of Inspectors. — The appropriate Government may appoint Inspectors for the`
  line `purposes of securing compliance with the provisions of this Act and any Inspector so appointed shall be`
  line `deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line `1 [ 17A. District Magistrate to implement the provisions. — The appropriate Government may confer`
  line `such powers and impose such duties on a District Magistrate as may be necessary, to ensure that the`
  line `provisions of this Act are properly carried out and the District Magistrate may specify the officer,`
  line `subordinate to him, who shall exercise all or any of the powers, and perform all or any of the duties, so`
  line `conferred or imposed and the local limits within which such powers or duties shall be carried out by th e`
  line `officer as may be prescribed.`
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line Gujarat
  line `Amendment of section 17A of 61 of 1986. — In the principal Act, in section 17A, -`
  line `(i) for the words “District Magistrate”, the words “District Magistrate, Municipal Commissioner,`
  line `Director of Labour or, as the case may be, the Regional Commissioner of Municipalities”`
  line `shall be substituted;`
  line `(ii) in the marginal note, for the word “District Magistrate”, the words “District Magistrate,`
  line `Municipal Commissioner, Director of Labour or Regional Commissioner of Municipalit ies”`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line `[ Vide Gujarat Act 19 of 2021, s. 4]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 2016, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-9
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Page 9`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  sourcePage 9
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `17B. Inspection and monitoring. — The appropriate Government shall make or cause to be made`
  line `periodic inspection of the places at which the employment of children is prohibited and hazardous`
  line `occupations or processes are carried out at such intervals as it thinks fit, and monitor the issues, relating to`
  line `the provisions of this Act.]`
  line `18. Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The appropriate Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazett e and subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules for carrying into eff ect the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of t he following matters, namely: —`
  line `1 [ ( a ) the conditions and the safety measures under clause ( b ) of sub - section ( 2 ) and other activities`
  line `under clause ( b ) to Explanation of sub - section ( 2 ) of section 3; ]`
  line `2 [ ( b ) ] the term of office of, the manner of filling casual vacancies of, and the allowances payable`
  line `to, the Chairman and members of the 3 [ Technical Advisory Committee ] and the conditions and`
  line `restrictions subject to which a non - member may be appointed to a sub - c ommittee under sub - section ( 5 )`
  line `of section 5;`
  line `4 [ ( c ) ] number of hours for which a 5 [ adolescent ] may be required or permitted to work unde r sub -`
  line `section ( 1 ) of section 7;`
  line `6 [ ( d ) ] grant of certificates of age in respect of young persons in employment or seeking`
  line `employment, the medical authorities which may issue such certificate, the form of such certificate, the`
  line `charges which may be made thereunder and the manner in which such cer tificate may be issued:`
  line `Provided that no charge shall be made for the issue of any such certificate if the application is`
  line `accompanied by evidence of age deemed satisfact ory by the authority concerned;`
  line `7 [ ( e ) ] the other particulars which a register maintaine d under section 11 should contain.`
  line `8 [ ( f ) the manner of payment of amount to the child or adolescent under sub - section ( 4 ) of section`
  line 14B;
  line `( g ) the manner of composition of the offence and payment of amount to the appropriate`
  line `Government under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 14D;`
  line `( h ) the powers to be exercised and the duties to be performed by the officer specified and the local`
  line `limits within which such powers or duties shall be carried out under section 17A. ]`
  line `19. Rules and notifications to be laid before Parliamen t or State legislature. — ( 1 ) Every rule made`
  line `under this Act by the Central Government and every notification issued under section 4, shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made or issued, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total`
  line `period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if,`
  line `before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or notif ication or both Houses agree that the rule`
  line `or notification should not be made or issued, the rule or notification shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 2016, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `2. Clause ( a ) rel ettered as clause ( b ) thereof by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for “Child Labour Technical Advisory Committee” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `4. Clause ( b ) relettered as clause ( c ) thereof by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for “child” (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `6. Clause ( c ) relettered as clause ( d ) thereof by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `7. Clause ( d ) relettered as clause ( e ) thereof by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 35 of 2016, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-10
