  title `Page 10`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or ann ulment`
  line `shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done u nder that rule or notification.`
  line `( 2 ) Every rule made by a State Government under this Act shall be laid as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before the legislature of that State.`
  line `20. Certain other provisions of law not barred. — Subject to the provisions contained in section 15,`
  line `the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of,`
  line `the provisions of the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948), the Plantations Labour Act, 1951 (69 of 1951) and`
  line `the Mines Act, 1952 (35 of 1952).`
  line `21. Power to remove difficulties. — ( 1 ) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removal of the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of three years from t he date on`
  line `which this Act receiv es the assent of the President.`
  line `( 2 ) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before the`
  line `Houses of Parliament.`
  line `22. Repeal and savings. — ( 1 ) The Employment of Children Act, 1938 (26 of 1938) is hereby r epealed.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done or`
  line `taken under the Act so repealed shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line `[ Sections 23 to 26.] — Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 2001 (30 of 2001), s. 2 and the First`
  line `Schedule ( w.e.f. 3 - 9 - 2001).`
